---
title: Mexican-Style Beef Albondigas Soup with Meatballs, Zucchini, Potatoes & Carrots
description: Celebrate Hispanic Heritage Month with this beefy Mexican-style meatball soup! The meatballs (albondigas) are seasoned with garlic and cumin, sizzled in a hot pan, then simmered in a hearty broth along with carrot, onion, oregano, zucchini, and potatoes. This delicious one-bowl meal just needs a final squeeze of lime juice for flavor perfection.
image: https://img.hellofresh.com/f_auto,fl_lossy,h_640,q_auto,w_1200/hellofresh_s3/image/66c38c855cb721784e6369b6-791a409e-5488e3be.jpeg
pdf: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipecards/card/66c38c855cb721784e6369b6-en-US.pdf
course: main course
source: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipes/mexican-style-beef-albondigas-soup-66c38c855cb721784e6369b6
author: HelloFresh
time required: 40m
nutrition:
  calories: 670 kcal
  fat: 32 g
  saturated fat: 10 g
  carbohydrates: 62 g
  sugar: 14 g
  protein: 33 g
  fiber: 7 g
  sodium: 3000 mg
servings: 2
---

Wash and dry produce.

Halve, peel, and dice @onion{1}(peeled and diced) into ½-inch pieces. Peel, trim, and quarter @carrots{3%ounce} lengthwise; cut crosswise into ½-inch-thick quarter-moons. Trim and quarter @zucchini{1}(trimmed and quartered) lengthwise; cut crosswise into ½-inch-thick quarter-moons. Halve and dice @potatoes{12%ounce}(peeled and diced) into ½-inch pieces. Quarter @lime{1}(quartered).

In a large #bowl{}, combine @ground beef{10%ounce}, @garlic powder{1%tsp}, @cumin{1%tsp}, @panko breadcrumbs{1/4%cup}, half the @beef stock concentrate{1%unit}, ¾ tsp @salt{3/4%tsp}, and @black pepper{1%tsp}. Gently combine, then form into 8-10 2-inch meatballs.

> 16-20 meatballs for 4 servings.

Heat a drizzle of @cooking oil{2%tsp} in a large, #heavy-bottomed pot{} over medium-high heat. Add onion, carrot, and zucchini; cook until veggies are golden and slightly softened, ~{3-4%minutes}. Add @dried oregano{1%tsp} and cook, stirring, until fragrant, ~{30%seconds} more.

Add potatoes, @sun-dried tomato paste{1%ounce}, 2 tsp @salt{2%tsp}, and pepper. Cook, stirring, until veggies are well coated, ~{1-2%minutes}. Add @veggie stock concentrate{1%unit}, @beef stock concentrate{1%unit}, and 3 1/2 cups water; bring to a boil.

Meanwhile, heat a drizzle of oil in a large pan over medium-high heat. Add meatballs and cook, turning occasionally, until browned all over, ~{2-3%minutes}.

> You may need to work in batches for 4 servings.

Transfer to a #paper-towel-lined plate{} (they'll finish cooking in the next step).

Reduce heat under pot with soup to low and carefully add meatballs one at a time. Cover and cook, stirring occasionally, until potatoes are tender and meatballs are fully cooked, ~{10-15%minutes}.

Remove from heat; taste and season with salt and pepper. Using a #spoon{}, skim any excess fat from the surface.

Stir in juice from half the lime wedges.

Divide soup between #bowls{} and serve with remaining lime wedges on the side.